I came in with high expectations, but they under delivered.
The food was okayish but it wasn't worth the money.
The aalu paratha was tasty.
The fried rice was alright but the vegetables in it weren't cooked properly.
The manchow soup was okay, not bad and not good.
The service was okay, but the part where I was annoyed is that they didn't provide a fork with the spoon, so it was kind of annoying there. I expect a fork in a restaurant this scale.
It felt unnecessarily fancy and not worth the money.
But it's okay, decent experience.

I am here in Goa for work and am glad to have found Navtara restaurant in Mapusa.I have visited multiple times and  have tried a decent variety of dishes (souht indian,roti sabji,cold beverages,desserts and last but not the least the strawberry season -shrikhand,cream,milkshake etc)One of the restaurant which serves good quality food and not to miss its service.Mr. Ramjeet who handles the orders and serving of last seating section of the restaurant is one of their efficient employee.He does give a personal touch of service to his customers.The ambience of the restaurant could be a little better however no complaints as nothing is unpleasant.The entire team of Navtara keep the good going :)
Staff not paying attention to your order unless you order 5-6 dishes. Food quality is okay. Quantity is good.
